Comparative material : Fragment from IdO- 401 ( holotype of
Aplysina ocracea
).

Skeleton : Choanosome formed by an irregular polygonal reticulation of spongin fibers, 37–275 Μm thick (average 92 Μm;
Fig. 6 D
). They have an amber coloured bark, with the exception of specimen MNRJ 5471 which is reddish coloured. The pith can be black or amber, with thickness of 10–60 Μm (average 26 Μm;
Fig. 6
E).
